<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-82-1233 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Government's proposals rest on six principal considerations: Decisionson energy supply must be oriented towards the market's needs. Competitionis the best guarantee for the preservation of consumer interests. Suitableregulations must promote competition, act as a watchdog on prices andprotect the interests of the consumer in all areas in which a naturalmonopoly must continue to exist. Technical security and an unbroken supplymust be provided. Consumers must be given not only assurances but alsoextra rights. All employees of the industry must have the opportunityfor direct participation in their future, for new career prospects andfor autonomous management of their economic affairs without interventionby the state. (orig./HSCH).</TEXT></DOC>